1. Files not found error 

The main issues we encountered while building the game were mostly related to **missing or mislocated 
assets**, such as background and hero images, which caused Phaser to throw “file not found” errors. 
These were often due to **incorrect folder structures, capitalization mismatches in file names, 
or wrong file types**. Additionally, the **scene imports in the main game file** were not aligned with

the actual file locations, preventing the Hero Selection screen from being loaded. 
There were also challenges with **pixel art styling and UI consistency**, 

including making buttons visually appealing with hover effects, drop shadows, and glowing indicators
to guide the player. Finally, ensuring a **smooth flow between scenes**—from the Start screen
to Hero Selection and then to the Game Scene—required careful handling of interactions and asset 
loading to prevent crashes and make the game playable.

